	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4codes":[{"code":"BGO", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Bismuth-Germanate crystal detector"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" It is shaped as a 28 cm long cylinder with a"
		,"coaxial hole of a 6 cm diameter. Radial thickness of"
		,"the detector is 7 cm. The crystal is optically"
		,"divided into six sectors, each covering an azimuthal"
		,"angle of 60 degrees."
		,"The detection efficiency for 5.5 MeV gamma-rays is"
		,"about 70% with an energy resolution in the total"
		,"absorption peak of 8%."]
	}
